What is the difference between an ordered list and an unordered list in HTML?

There is a specific order in which the item(s) are ordered or sorted.
eg. an ordered list containing text can be sorted by length, alphebetical order

-Ordered list are created using the <ol>
  -attribute used with the <ol>
  element to specify the type of
  numbering (numbers, letters,roman numerals ).

  -unordered list are created using the <ul>
  attribute used with the <ul>
  element to specify the type of
  bullet point (circles, squares, diamonds)

BOOK STATES:
Ordered lists are lists where each item in the list is numbered.

eg., the list might be a set of steps for a recipe that must be performed in order,
or a legal contract where each point needs to be identified by a section number.


Is an HTML list a block element or an inline element?
block
